{
  "stem": "10496.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, then for a time I went to the Jewish school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But what happened with the Jewish school is that every time you turned around, the teachers were gone because they're trying to get away and-- and-- and emigrate.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So there was never a teacher around.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I would say that between 1935 and '42, I didn't get much of an education.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the older generation, I think they were-- you know, the older generation were OK.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In other words, they-- they sympathized my-- with my parents and all that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the younger generations, what-- that was the problem.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The younger generation were indoctrinated in the-- in the-- in the schools, and indoctrinated to Nazism and whatever it stands for.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so we already see a lot of discrimination.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, even I, when I was-- I was in second or third grade, I already had to worry about when I leave the classroom that I wouldn't be attacked by some-- by some of these Hitler youth.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So, you know, so it-- it was really-- I really was upset about that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I think-- let me put it this way, that-- what I experienced.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, I wasn't really safe.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In other words, whenever-- in other words, I walked out of my house.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And let's say I would go to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then on the way back, some-- some of these kids would-- would attack me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And many times I was-- I was saved because my father came just in time to break it up.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But I remember once that when we went into-- into the house when I thought I was safe, and I walked in-- into the house, there were already two or three kids, Nazis, that were awaiting-- bless you-- waiting for-- for-- for me.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And, you know, it's-- this is the type of discrimination that happened.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Or if-- if a policeman was-- was somewhere on a corner and he saw me being beaten up, you know, he would look the other way.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In other words, I-- there was no police protection for me at all.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I had to sort of work it on my own.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You're talking about Karlsruhe?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, the-- the point is this, that Hitler, when he got into power, it was very soon he started to, first of all, confiscate all the Jewish businesses.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and then all the professionals, Jewish professionals, whether it's-- whether they were teachers or professors or-- or scientists, they were-- they lost their-- they lost their jobs.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They lost their jobs.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In other words-- no matter how good they were.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- and then, of course, later on we had to have a Jewish-- an ID card.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, oh, in 1935, the-- we were-- what do they call-- we were not citizen-- German citizens anymore.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They took away our German citizenship.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So that sort of gave us an idea-- gave a lot of people idea that it's not-- it's not a good place to stay anymore.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My Uncle Julius.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then my Uncle Sally followed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's two.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then my Uncle Albert moved to Argentina, so that was three.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and then my-- you know, my father, of course, we got out later on, you know?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But that's--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because he felt that the-- that Hitler would not touch him as a-- as--as a war veteran.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, he fought almost the entire war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that he-- and he had-- he had the Iron Cross, so he thought that he would be safe.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But as far as Hitler's concerned, it's nobody safe.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Not anyone that's Jewish or gypsy or whatever.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, she-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] she was, of course, a Russian national.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she-- she did pretty much what her father-- what my father did.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In other words, she followed my father loyally.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So whatever my father believe in, she backed him up.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- but as-- as we found out that it made no difference at all.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I was brought up orthodox.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In other words, we-- there were two synagogues in-- in Karlsruhe.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One was orthodox and the other was reform.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, all I can say is I think one was on Karlsruhe Strasse--",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--and and the other one, I don't even remember now where-- where that--",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think it was the Karlsruhe Strasse, the one that-- the orthodox.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it's a very nice synagogue.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's very-- you know, very elaborate inside with-- the-- the bima was in the middle, rather than in front.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there were balconies for the women.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, orthodox, that's what-- you know, what happened, you know, the separation of-- of men and women.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we had-- we had some very good times.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I mean, a lot of Jewish holidays.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were very active in the beginning.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
